{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2c7dc143-5cf2-4609-a3ea-c8e344d3809f","content":"The project path doesn't exist yet, but here's what you need to configure in your `.csproj` to publish as a **dotnet tool**:\n\n### Required `.csproj` properties\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server for ...</Description>\n  <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n1. **`PackAsTool`** — marks the project as a dotnet tool.\n2. **`ToolCommandName`** — the CLI name users invoke (e.g., `my-mcp-server`).\n3. **`OutputType` must be `Exe`** — required for stdio transport.\n\n### Publish steps\n\n```bash\n# Pack\ndotnet pack -c Release\n\n# Push to NuGet.org (get API key from nuget.org/account/apikeys)\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY \\\n  --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Users install & run with\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server    # runs via stdio\n```\n\nWant me to scaffold the project with these settings?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f1d63a79-9336-4d9a-aa31-30df06347666","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project doesn't exist yet. The user is asking what they need to configure to publish a C# MCP server as a dotnet tool. This is a guidance question, not an implementation task. Let me give them the key configuration points.","outputTokens":500,"requestId":"B020:38FB84:13EE9EE:165485C:6A027DC8"},"id":"a36b241d-ec5c-4a04-b73e-30f29b58f382","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:09:38.898Z","parentId":"e522a8e5-d5e9-43da-abab-b8cf67a06b89"}
